qx|o9|pn|sdoty,sdoty,sdoty,sdoty|st||md|1SAK3HKJ54DA8CT972,S976HAQ3DJT95C654,SQJ542H86DK32CKQ8,ST8HT972DQ764CAJ3,|rh||ah|Board 9|mb|1N|mb|p|mb|2H|an|xfer to 2!S: 5+!S, any strength|mb|p|mb|2S|mb|p|mb|3N|an|10-14 with exactly 5!S|mb|p|mb|4S|an|3+ spades|mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|nt|^B@2^Z@3Here responder's 3NT rebid shows game values (10-14 points) with exactly a 5 card spade suit. It sends the message: "partner we belong in game, but I don't know whether we should play in spades or in NT. Do you have a fit for my suit?" As before, if opener has 3+ card support for responder's major, he takes it back to that suit.|pg||pc|DJ|mc|9|pg||nt||


qx|o10|pn|sdoty,sdoty,sdoty,sdoty|st||md|1SQJ43H76DQJ4CAKQ4,ST876HQ8DAT2C9865,SAK2HKJ543D865C32,S95HAT92DK973CJT7,|rh||ah|Board 10|mb|1N|mb|p|mb|2D|an|xfer to 2!H: 5+!H, any strength|mb|p|mb|2H|mb|p|mb|3N|an|10-14 with exactly 5!H|mb|p|mb|p|an|only 2 hearts|mb|p|nt|^B@2^Z@3 Opener isn't in love with hearts, but he still bids 2@H as partner asked him to. Responder's 3NT rebid says "we have the points for game, and I have exactly a five card heart suit. Should we play in 3NT or 4@H partner?" Opener's pass says,  "we don't have a heart fit, so let's play game in no trump." |pg||nt|^B@2^Z@3 If you only take away one idea from this lecture, the most important one is the following: |pg||nt|^B@2^Z@3 With the points to invite or force to game, responder never insists on playing in his 5 card major suit. He always gives opener the option of playing in no trump instead, because he (responder) can't be sure that they have an 8 card fit. |pg||at|^B@2^Z@3 This means that opener has to be on the ball, though. If responder transfers and then rebids no trump, it isn't because he wants to play in no trump. If he just wanted to play in no trump, he wouldn't have bothered telling you about his major suit.|pg||nt|^B@2^Z@3 If responder transfers and rebids notrump, it is because he needs you to decide whether the partnership belongs in the major (if you have 3+ card support) or in NT if you only have a doubleton. |pg||at|^B@2^Z@3 If opener has 3+ card support, HE IS EXPECTED TO GO BACK TO RESPONDER'S MAJOR. That's very important. If opener doesn't do that, then the whole thing falls apart. There's definitely some partnership trust involved in these transfer auctions.|pg||pc|C8|mc|9|pg||nt||

