qx|o11|pn|sdoty,sdoty,sdoty,sdoty|st||md|1SA9HK74DAK94CK952,SKQ5HQT32DJT8CQ87,SJT8432HAJ6DQ7C63,S76H985D6532CAJT4,|RH||AH|Board  11|mb|1N|mb|p|mb|2H|an|xfer to 2!S: 5+!S, any strength|mb|p|mb|2S|mb|p|mb|3S|an|inv (8-9) with 6+!S|mb|p|mb|4S|an|accepting invite|mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|nt|^B@2^Z@3With 8+ points, the only time that responder gets to INSIST on playing in his major suit is when he has at least 6 of them. Because with 6, he knows that the partnership is -guaranteed- an 8+ card fit... even if opener only has a doubleton. |PG||AT|
^B@2^Z@3Responder's 3@S rebid says "We are playing in spades-I've got 6+ of them. But I need to know whether we should stop in a part score or go to game." Opener is maximum and will take it to game.|
pg||pc|DJ|mc|11|pg||


qx|o12|pn|sdoty,sdoty,sdoty,sdoty|st||md|1SKJ3HK9DQ762CAQ96,SAT85HQ6DA95CJT82,S72HAT8754DJ43CK7,SQ964HJ32DKT8C543,|rh||ah|Board 12|mb|1N|mb|p|mb|2D|an|xfer to 2!H: 5+!H, any strength|mb|p|mb|2H|mb|p|mb|3H|an|inv (8-9) with 6+!H|mb|p|mb|p|an|rejecting invite|mb|p|nt|^B@2^Z@3With a 6 card heart suit responder can invite on playing in hearts --- his 3@H bid asks opener to choose between 3@H and 4@H. Opener is minimum with 2@H and rejects the invitation by passing.|at|
^B@2^Z@3With a 5+ card major, responder's bidding options are determined by two key things: |pg||cp|8|at|
^CHis overall strength, and; |pg||cp|8|at|
^CHis major suit length.|PG||nt|^B@2^Z@3 If  WEAK 0-7 points.|PG||cp|8|at|
Transfer then pass = 5+ card major suit (hoping for a 5-3 or 5-4 fit, but once in a while you'll end up in a 5-2. That's OK.|pg||nT|^B@2^Z@3 If INVITATIONAL with 8-9 points.|PG||CP|8|AT|
* Transfer then 2NT = inviting game with a 5 card major. Asks opener to choose between playing in the major or in no trump, and between a part score or game. OR |PG||AT|
* Transfer then 3 of the major = inviting game with a 6+ card major. notrump isn't an option-opener just chooses between 3M or 4M.|pg||nt|^B@2^Z@3 If GAME FORCING with 10-14 points.|PG||CP|8|AT|
   ** Transfer then 3NT = game values with exactly a 5 card major. Asks opener to choose between 3NT and 4M, depending on whether he has a fit for responder. OR |PG||AT|
   **  Transfer then a new suit = game values, exactly 5 cards in the major and   4+ cards in the second suit. Gives opener a choice of games.|pg||pc|CJ|mc|9|pg||nt||
