qx|o14|pn|sdoty,sdoty,sdoty,sdoty|st||md|1S82HAQJ6DKQ93CKT4,SJ7HT874DJ754CA53,SKQ965H5DA62CQJ72,SAT43HK932DT8C986,|RH||AH|Board 14|mb|1N|mb|p|mb|2H|an|xfer to 2!S: 5+!S, any strength|mb|p|mb|2S|mb|p|mb|3C|an|natural, game forcing|mb|p|mb|3N|mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|nt|^B@2^Z@3In this example, opener does not have a fit for responder's spade suit. He also has strong holdings in both hearts and diamonds. So, even though responder doesn't rate to have much in the red suits, opener can comfortably place the contract in 3NT and responder doesn't have to worry about passing, because he knows that opener has a good idea of what his hand is like.|pg||pc|D4|mc|10|pg||nt||
