qx|o15|pn|sdoty,sdoty,sdoty,sdoty|st||md|1SA72HKQ52DAT94CK4,ST4HJT96DKQ72C653,SKQJ65HA8D53CAQJ2,S983H743DJ86CT987,|rh||ah|Board 15|mb|1N|mb|p|at|	
^B@2^Z@3Responder has a fantastic hand here, and definitely wants to get to slam. However, he needs to figure out where the partnership belongs... in spades? No trump? maybe even clubs? There's no need for responder to go blasting into the atmosphere right away ... he can take it slow and steady to get the information he needs.|pg||mb|2H|an|xfer to 2!S: 5+!S, any strength|mb|p|mb|2S|nt|
^B@2^Z@3He starts with a simple Jacoby Transfer, to establish that he has a spade suit. He follows it up with a 3@C bid-natural and game forcing. Opener's next bid is going to determine where responder goes from here. When opener bids 3@S, responder knows they have a spade fit-a key piece of information, since now he knows where they should play in (spades). |pg||mb|p|mb|3C|an|natural, game forcing|mb|p|mb|3S|an|3+!S|mb|p|nt|
^B@2^Z@3Over 3@S (which sets spades as trump), responder bids 4@C-this is a control showing cuebid. It also shows responder's slam interest.|pg||mb|4C|an|cuebid|mb|p|mb|4D|an|cuebid|mb|p|nt|
^B@2^Z@3 Once opener cooperates with a 4@D cuebid, responder knows that all of the side suits are under control and he can continue with (RKC) Blackwood. I'm using RKC 1430 today, but this 4NT bid would be whatever kind of blackwood you and your partner have agreed to use. |pg||mb|4N|an|RKC 1430|mb|p|mb|5H|an|2 keycards no !SQ|mb|p|mb|5N|an|specific kings?|mb|p|mb|7S|an|if you're asking for kings, we can bid 7|mb|p|mb|p|mb|p|nt|
^B@2^Z@3I don't want to get too caught up in the bidding after 4NT ... that's a topic for another day. The important bids are the ones leading up to 4NT....
NS have a solid, straightforward, NATURAL auction.  Responder doesn't need to go jumping around or try to come up with anything fancy. He uses a nice natural sequence to describe his hand and find out whether or not there's a spade fit and it leaves the partnership plenty of room to exchange information.|pg||pc|DK|mc|13|pg||

